{
  "doc_id": "19433",
  "text": "In human bone metastases, Wwox, showing localization in the Golgi apparatus, might be implicated in HIF-1α translocation and stabilization leading to HIF-1 activity in bone metastasis [CITATION_1] . It is known that in primary carcinomas HIF-1α stabilization depends on a hypoxic niche and/or oncogene activation; growth factors including HGF induce HIF-1α mRNA, transactivation, and protein expression through NF-κB and HIF-1 autoregulatory loop [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
